The paper discusses a new multiagent reinforcement learning algorithm that allows agents to reach a Nash Equilibrium in benchmark games with minimum knowledge. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the dynamics of the algorithm and how the policies of multiple learning agents evolve over time, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the numerical solution of the algorithm's differential equations, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
